      shin_r:            { name: "Shin", pain: 5, feels: "Scratching, moderate bone vibration", why: "Tibia bone close to surface, thin skin", heal: "2-3 weeks", tip: "Avoid bumping your shins during healing (easier said than done). Socks should be loose around the top.", desc: "The shin has the tibia bone relatively close to the surface with moderate skin thickness. It's not as bad as people expect — the front is worse than the sides where there's more muscle." },
